Package org.jfree.chart.plot

Class MultiplePiePlot

java.lang.Object
org.jfree.chart.block.AbstractContentBlock
org.jfree.chart.plot.Plot
org.jfree.chart.plot.MultiplePiePlot
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, EventListener, Block, ContentBlock, AxisChangeListener, LegendItemSource, DatasetChangeListener, org.jfree.ui.Drawable, org.jfree.util.PublicCloneable
public class MultiplePiePlot extends Plot implements Block, Cloneable, Serializable
A plot that displays multiple pie plots using data from a CategoryDataset.

    • prefetchSectionPaints

      private void prefetchSectionPaints()
      For each key in the dataset, check the sectionPaints cache to see if a paint is associated with that key and, if not, fetch one from the drawing supplier. These colors are cached so that the legend and all the subplots use consistent colors.
